                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Knipple</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Alvis</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Nine prisoners escaped from the local jail Monday night. Six were caught,
                    but Ayres, Knipple, and Alvis remain at large.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Keep Your Faith</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Come forward then promptly and do not let it be said that the farmers of
                    Augusta refused to sell their produce. . . but rather let her, in this patriotic
                    purpose, be proclaimed the Banner County of the Banner State."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The editor calls on Augusta farmers to comply with the law and with the
                    resolutions Augusta citizens passed voluntarily. In these proclamations, the
                    farmers promised not to hoard their produce but to sell it at the agreed upon
                    rates.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>News from the Valley</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Imboden</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>General</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>General Imboden attacked the enemy at Charlestown, Jefferson County, last
                    Sunday, drove the Yankees out of town, and captured 434 prisoners and supplies.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
